Example
Scroll the document to the horizontal position "500":

Copy
window.scrollTo(500, 0);

Description
The scrollTo() method scrolls the document to the specified coordinates.

Use the scrollBy() method to scroll a specified distance multiple times.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
scrollTo()	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
window.scrollTo(x_pos, y_pos)
Parameter Values
Parameter
Type
Description
x_pos

Number

Required.
The coordinate to scroll to horizontally, in pixels
y_pos

Number

Required.
The coordinate to scroll to vertically, in pixels
Return Value
No return value

More Examples
Scroll the document to position "300" horizontally and "500" vertically:

Copy
window.scrollTo(300, 500);
